  "body": "### Component\r\n\r\nForge\r\n\r\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\r\n\r\n- [X] Foundry\r\n- [X] Foundryup\r\n\r\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\r\n\r\n_No response_\r\n\r\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\r\n\r\n`forge coverage` \r\n\r\n### Operating System\r\n\r\nNone\r\n\r\n### Describe the bug\r\n\r\ncoverage crashes while analyzing contracts, because it relies on incorrect source maps produced by `--ir-minimum`. Panic occurs while indexing the sourcefile loaded in memory\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ forge coverage --ir-minimum --contracts src/\r\n\r\n[⠒] Compiling...\r\n[⠘] Compiling 63 files with 0.8.20\r\n[⠃] Solc 0.8.20 finished in 12.01s\r\nCompiler run successful!\r\nAnalysing contracts...\r\nThe application panicked (crashed).\r\nMessage:  byte index 13549 is out of bounds of `// SPDX-License-Identifier: MIT\r\npragma solidity ^0.8.20;\r\n\r\n// rest of contract`\r\n```",
